diary_text: Sung completely blind.  She just played the karaoke 6 times and each time laid down a new track.  When she was doing it<COMMA> it sounded like she had finally flipped and gone sick in the head.  Just loaded all tracks into the DAW<COMMA> and the result is amazing.  Only Latincita is capable of something like this.  Only thing that sucks is what she<QUOTE>s saying with this song.  It<QUOTE>s cool none the less.

critics_review: From the lost Radio show "Last Day of January 2018".  Fourth take of the song<COMMA> and an absolute masterpiece.
diary_text: Days before she was kicked out and forced to move in with Fle.  And<COMMA> the day Bram came back to Holland (?)  Everything went wrong that day.  Kids had been messing with mixer.  No sound on one channel.  No output to engineering.  Then<COMMA> USB Stick with recording got corrupted.  All files were lost for months until recovery software was found that could read some of the MP3<QUOTE>s.<CR><CR>After the recording she says:  "You recorded the other one<COMMA> right? The first one.  Now then stop it then and work with that.  It<QUOTE>s too late.  My voice is tired.  I want to scream<COMMA> but I<QUOTE>m not in the studio.  Anyways.  Let me see what you make with that. Ok. Maybe you make something nice. With what I gave you."

critics_review: Latincita<QUOTE>s first Reggaeton.  Text by Latincita. All voices by Latincita.<CR><CR>Pista De Reggaeton Perreo Brutal Electro Party 2017 - AR MUSIC LOS GALACTICOS
diary_text: Latincita<QUOTE>s first studio recording in years.  Nothing was setup and ready anymore for doing a multi-track recording<COMMA> so Latincita just recorded the karaoke 5 times<COMMA> each with a different voice.  She couldn<QUOTE>t hear the other voices<COMMA> so I guess she just imagined them while she was singing.  The end result is that nothing can be fixed or edited.  It is what it is<COMMA> unfortunately.

critics_review: Climbing back through the mirror<COMMA> Latincita comes to visit all of us on the sad dark black and white world of the ordinary livers of this world<COMMA> and leaves behind a gem.   If we dare to face its brilliance and let it show us colors we never imagined existed<COMMA> …we push play.
diary_text: Following God<QUOTE>s commands<COMMA> I hooked up all as he told me to.  USB to Control-Room to audio in on the Soundcraft.  Master-out back to track 7 on the Alesis<COMMA> and mute ON.  Richard via wireless from headphone 1 to the sennheiser ear-buds.  Latincita on headphone 2 to garbage white ear-buds.  The black cable to channel 7 and to Latincitas<QUOTE>s Sennheiser.  The silver on 6 to the AKG.  Two mikes.  One for Latincita<COMMA> another to feed her energy through the echo machine.   Then three tracks and all the effects he told me to use<COMMA> with the levels set as he wanted.  Tiny Expand on her recording.  With a bit of 500Hz boost and 3K cut to warm it<COMMA> and get rid of that stupid brilliance and crackle.  Then the audio twice on either channel<COMMA> with pure L and 30% right on the left and the opposite on the right.  Strong 4dB bass.  Studio Reverb<COMMA> 70% wet.  -18dB: as low as possible<COMMA> but still enough punch. And as wide as possible.<CR><CR>A masterpiece is born.   Something I never ever want to hear.  Dry tears.  Silent pain.

critics_review: Latincita has always had one talent.  A special talent.  She listens<COMMA> remembers and duplicates.  A copy of what she heard.  A perfect copy<COMMA> but still 100% pure Latincita.  Maybe it’s making it sound like it always should have sounded.  The Angels can sing. You know.  Make more beautiful sounds than our minds can comprehend.  Latincita has been many places.  Terrible places.  Magical places.  She’s heard many many things.  Perhaps things our minds can’t comprehend.  She listens<COMMA> she remembers and she duplicates.    Hasta Que te Conocí …copied for us by Latincita
A new version of this one
diary_text: This is the original Mexican version.  The other was the Spanish version.  By that Spanish woman who was very famous singing this song.  She came to Venezuela about 4 time singing this song.  That is the oher one.  This one is by Juan Gariel out of Mexico.  He is dead<COMMA> but he was very famous<COMMA> gay and everything.  There is also the Bachatta version.  No one ever did the Bachatta.  We could do that.  Bachatta is very popular.  It could be good.  A Bachatta version.

article_title: Latincita - La Lupe - Qué Te Pedí
critics_review: Stars<COMMA> summer breeze<COMMA> white foamy waves spraying salty sea water up on the beach<COMMA> the water glistens and shimmers in the moonlight<COMMA> warm wet sand between your toes<COMMA> whisky with ice in your hands<COMMA> as Latincita sings away.  The heavens open up.  The stars burn brighter and brighter.  The planets slowly start to dance.  Move to every note Latincita lets loose<COMMA>  Defying quantum mechanics<COMMA> energy transcending space and time.  Driving the heavens and stars.  Angelic music the ancients sought with all their algebra and trigonometry<COMMA> but never found.  The power of the universe.  The love Latincita has in her heart.  A power trapped inside.  Waiting for the moment.  Waiting for now.  Waiting for Latincita to arrive.  To leave her mark and transform the universe from this moment on.

Acariciame<COMMA> Enloqueceme<COMMA> Ameme<COMMA> Ahogame<COMMA> Cuidame<COMMA> Matame<COMMA> Mirame<COMMA> Muriendome<COMMA> Acariciame<COMMA> Empapame<COMMA> Contagiame<COMMA> Acariciame<COMMA> Robame<COMMA> Dominame<COMMA> Acariciame<COMMA> Tomame<COMMA> Teniendome<COMMA> Acariciame<COMMA> Empapame<COMMA> Contagiame<COMMA> Acariciame<COMMA> Hacerme<COMMA> Contagiame<COMMA> Acariciame.

Somewhere there exists a mirror where our dreams are reality.  The world there on the other side of the mirror is exactly as we so desperately want it to be.  For nearly everyone on this earth<COMMA> that world on the other side of the mirror is a dream world.  Only in our dreams will we ever visit it.  There is one<COMMA> however<COMMA> who is walking quietly unnoticed between us.  For her<COMMA> the mirror world is not at all a magic place.  She can step back and forth without even realizing it.  More importantly<COMMA> she can take those around her<COMMA> with her.  Grab Latincita’s hand<COMMA> and step through.  This recording I made with a tiny laptop speaker.  There was no music.  Only her voice.  And it sounded like it was underwater.  What I didn’t realize is that was I was just on the wrong side of the mirror.  Let’s go back to the 10th of July 2011 and listen to the recording again<COMMA> on her side of the mirror.
diary_text: No clue how I recorded this.  It sounds like it was recorded on a small laptop-mike somewhere on the other side of the room.  In my mind we were in the small bedroom upstairs with the fancy new studio mike and a tube pre-amp.  Doesn<QUOTE>t at all explain this awful recording. Crazy to think Karin recorded this the day before Latincita appeared on this earth*. Crazier still to think that Karin was born only 30 kilometers due south of where I was born.  Insane thing is that Karin was only 20 years old when she recorded this. [I was 13]    <CR><CR>* https://carpenters.amcorner.com/album/close-to-you

critics_review: Third of the Trio of shows in July 2025. <CR><CR>After the other worldly performance that Latincita produced during Kwaku 2023<COMMA> this years show was truly sad<COMMA> as Alina and Vanessa effectively drained nearly every drop of energy from Latincita.  They took over the show and stole all the great songs.  What could have been a glorius peformances of Latincita<QUOTE>s Nadie se Muere<COMMA> Yerberito Moderno en Flor Pálida<COMMA> was transformed into a terrible mess of a Cuba Music show.
diary_text: The usual nightmare of parking in Amsterdam was brought to the next level with the news that Arno was following a training in Schiedam and so needed to live 24x7 with the love of his life for the next three weeks util he started his new job.  Latincita quit her dream job at CanAdelaar since Arno could soon take care of her<COMMA> just as she got the news that she was getting an electric car so she could go to the work she no longer had.<CR><CR>To add to the fun<COMMA> the sun moved down to shine directly behind the podium so that nothing was visible on the camera monitor.  Didn<QUOTE>t matter.  The show was a mess<COMMA> and who wanted to see the fabulous body in that gorgeous black dress that Arno would be enjoying soon after the show anyway.

critics_review: Second of the Trio of shows in July 2025.   This time on a large podium in front of the restaurants on the Haven of Almere.  The audience loved every minute of the show.  Not as much fun as Vlaardingen<COMMA> but the band was simply out of this world.

critics_review: A super cool - next level - show ... on a fake beach ... near the Haven of Vlaardingen.

Turned out to be one of the best shows ever ... total next level.  <CR><CR>And no Arno.  And also<COMMA> for some strange reason<COMMA> Arno was not there.  But Noah and Thijs en Noella were !!!  And Donato and Ruwena were there but Ruwena said the music was too load<COMMA> so they parked themselves way at the back of the lot<COMMA> and smoked and drank while Latincita gave one hell of a performance without them.<CR><CR>Locked myself out of the house and had to run all the way from the Gorzen to Vlaardingen<COMMA> so completely missed the first number (Cogele el Gusto).

Latincita had a killer outfit and gave one hell of a show.

critics_review: Bigger than this it doesn<QUOTE>t get in Holland.  Performing for an audience of thousands from all over the world<COMMA> Los Elegantes got a full 15 minutes to blow the socks off of Rotterdam.

In the pouring rain with a huge audience cheering away in a tent all the way behind the field where they were supposed to stand<COMMA> Los Elegantes does their best to chase away the clouds with their fabulous mix of Latin Music.  Eventually they succeed and the party moves back out to the field where it belongs.  Alina and Latincita and the band give everyone a great show.  Enjoy Kwaku Festival with the fantastic Los Elegantes Caribeños (the full orchestra) at one of Hollands oldest Music Festivals.
diary_text: Because of the rain<COMMA> was forced to film pressed against the podium 3" from the monitors<COMMA> so sound was anything but great.  However<COMMA> a miracle occurred and Ruben shared a feed from the board<COMMA> which was mixed with the camera recording to produce this sound-track.<CR><CR>Concert itself was mindblowing.  Ruben never told the band this was a major festival and they would be performing on a huge podium to a large audience.  Everything seemed to come out of nowhere.  Pouring rain magically turned into sunshine and dancing public.<CR><CR>Only downside is that Alina turned everything into a "CUBA" show.  Even Llorarás was accordig to her from Cuba.  Latincita stole the show however with her cool outfit and space shoes from China.

Alina finally arrived back from Cuba to join Latincita on stage to delver a star-studded show in front of a slimmed down orchestra with only Ruben on Keyboards<COMMA> a brand new Guitarist and a great Bassist<COMMA> and 5 Percussionists.  <CR><CR>Even though they missed the Brass Section or a second Keyboard<COMMA> the audience had a fabulous time<COMMA> dancing and playing along hours after the official Musicon closing time.

Every reahersal was a mess<COMMA> but somehow they managed to pull everything together for this show.<CR><CR>Just before the show<COMMA> Latincita was complaining about some unbearable severe pain somewhere. La Diva showed up as well<COMMA> and so there were two other girls plus Walter.  And a dying Latincita.  ....and no space anymore on stage for Latincita to dance.

critics_review: Sound was a wreck<COMMA> but the old peaple had a great time. And the performance … without Walter … was great. It is what it is.  La Parranda screwed up by the sound-guy.<CR><CR>Guest performer from the public on Congo<QUOTE>s and John<QUOTE>s sax sola made for a fun end to the show.
diary_text: A complete and utter disaster as far as the sound was concerned. critics_review: What is the definition of a “concert” ... when a female singer fills the heavens with non-ending out of this world sounds<COMMA> while kids run wild<COMMA> market sellers clean up their junk<COMMA> the electricity is slowly shut off and all ends with a bang.   If that’s the definition... Latincita gave a great one last night.  I was there<COMMA> but no matter how many times I listen<COMMA> I just can’t convince myself that she actually did this “live”.  No tricks or strange effects.  Just giving her “spring show” as she says.  Enjoy more than one hour of Latincita.  Over a million years in far-away galaxies<COMMA> they’ll ask why they had to wait so long to hear something like this.  And why in God’s name was such a show only worth a white envelope with a few measly euro’s .. enough for Latincita to buy some soup for her family.

critics_review: Sit back and just enjoy.  Two hours of Latincita<COMMA> as she brings us on a long journey.  First class Salsa and Merengue to Sparkling Ballads<COMMA> to Mexican Cry your eyes out<COMMA> to best the 50’s have to offer and on to Mexico<COMMA> beautiful incredible things.  And after 2 and half hours when you ask ... how can someone do that for so long.  It stops.  But I guarantee you<COMMA> it only stops because she wore out all the transistors and capacitors and resistors in her mixer.  It crashed and stopped recording<COMMA> but Latincita went on and on and on.     Radio Bienvenido 2017   ...her best radio yet.

A trip along masterpiece after masterpiece.  Real Latincita including all the mistakes and nuttiness.  And the genius.<CR><CR>This is Latincita’s show.  She finds the karaoke’s on YouTube and starts singing.  She needs about 5 seconds between each song to decide what she wants next and find it … and off…   Singing with her eyes closed.  No practice<COMMA> no cheating.  It’s all-in her head.  All she needs the karaoke’s for<COMMA> are so you can hear the music that’s in her head.  Otherwise you’d only hear her voice<COMMA> and she thinks you’d find that boring.<CR><CR>One hour+ of great music.
